<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="67f27da5-b317-5d6b-83ae-622b8ee6b181" activityNameId="2381524a-7b56-4ccd-a920-cf87e7b75f9f" parentActivityId="06ae14d7-18e5-533d-9dd5-4b23547c010a" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">treatment of waste, from silicon wafer production, inorganic, residual material landfill</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to water from leachate and long-term emissions to ground water). Expenditures for solidificalion with cement are also included.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of 'waste, from silicon wafer production, inorganic' in a residual material landfill (RMLF). Recommended use of this dataset: The waste is a mixture of various inorganic wastes generated during production of silicon wafers for photovoltaic cells.  Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% inorganic Waste Si wafer production; .  Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): H2O 93802; O 204810; H na; C 31490; S na; N na; P na; B na; Cl na; Br na; F 41160; I na; Ag na; As na; Ba na; Cd na; Co na; Cr na; Cu na; Hg na; Mn na; Mo na; Ni na; Pb na; Sb na; Se na; Sn na; V na; Zn na; Be na; Sc na; Sr na; Ti na; Tl na; W na; Si 585410; Fe na; Ca 43326; Al na; K na; Mg na; Na na.  Share of carbon in initial waste input that is biogenic 0%.  Additional solidification of residues with 0.4 kg of cement.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="5e736d13-58c6-4fbd-8157-dd6ef35c3f88">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">3822:Treatment and disposal of hazardous waste</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="81e54bf8-5993-5b5b-bc50-6978cab0c51f">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RoE</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents a landfill site with mean annual temperature (MAT) of 10.3897 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 960.474141305017 mm/year, mean annual actual evaporation (EAT) of 450.073365823956 mm/year, and net infiltration of 510.4 mm/year. The leachate percolating through the residual material landfill has an average residence time of 6.86 years.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Reference for climatic parameters:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">UN data, 2020. Precipitation, Environment Statistics Database, United Nations Statistics Division Available at: http://data.un.org/Data.aspx?q=precipitation&amp;d=ENV&amp;f=variableID%3a6; </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">World Bank, 2022. Surface area (sq.km), World Bank Group Available at: https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/AG.SRF.TOTL.K2</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Residual material landfill for polluted, inorganic waste (VVEA Type C). With base seal and leachate collection system. Ultimate average landfill height is 10 meters. Operation phase duration is 30 years. Recultivation after closure. Additional solidification with cement requested. Based on average waste composition and climate data the end of carbonate phase in the residual material landfill is estimated to be reached after 60 000 years.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2010-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
